properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 6 at 2:40AM EST until February 7 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt and seas 6 to 9 feet expected. For the Small Craft
Advisory, west winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and seas
5 to 8 feet expected.

* WHERE...Flagler Beach to Volusia-Brevard County Line 20-60 nm
and Volusia-Brevard County Line to Sebastian Inlet 20-60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 10 AM EST Friday. For the
Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM to 4 PM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST FRIDAY... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 4 PM EST FRIDAY
